Watkyns is best known for his performances with Arno Carstens and he is still a member of the Springbok Nude Girls. His session playing and songwriting credits include Mike Rutherford (Genesis, Mike and the Mechanics), Jack Hardman (Good Boy), Zolani Mahola (Freshlyground), Judith Sephuma, Jimmy Dludu, and upcoming Gabriela Diamond.Image supplied: David WatkynsDavid has performed across Africa, Europe and Asia, including Isle of Wight Festival (UK), St Paul's Cathedral (UK), Oppikoppi (SA), Rocking the Daisies (SA), and winner of MELA Award for Contribution by Youth to South African Music Industry.His music is influenced by Peter Gabriel, Chet Baker, Johnny Clegg, The 1975, New Radicals and Paul Simon.Watkyn’s music is story-driven with classic instrumentation, big trumpet solos, nostalgicsynthesizers and lyrics of love, lust and loss.His new single Education is out now - and I caught up with him last week… .bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} What is your job description?Songwriter, musician, entertainer..bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} What does music mean to you?Music is the one universal language we all understand and feel..bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} My music is about…Connecting, escaping, enjoyment, freedom..bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} Retirement will happen when… The musical journey never ends!.bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} I don't do… Swimming if I can’t see the bottom….bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} I would love to co-write with… Gregg Alexander, Andrew Wyatt, Paul Simon and David Kramer..bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} Where do you go for inspiration to create?I find inspiration in my everyday experiences and memories, my friends, and looking back at history. .bizicon + br{display:none} h2 .bizicon img{top:10px !important} What i